- Shi Guang!
- Shi Guang!

54
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,039
Your father is actually
a successor of Pinsanxian.

55
00:02:58,159 --> 00:03:00,120
Why didn't you say such
an impressive thing earlier?

56
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,039
Pinsanxian isn't

57
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:03,159
some exclusive secret of our family.

58
00:03:03,439 --> 00:03:05,080
Many people in Yulin know
a thing or two about it.

59
00:03:05,199 --> 00:03:06,240
What's there to be proud of?

60
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,680
It's not the same. Yours is authentic.

61
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,360
What's authentic or not?

62
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:13,080
Simply put,

63
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,479
Pinsanxian is just a cooking method.

64
00:03:14,879 --> 00:03:16,360
Mixing meat and vegetables together.

65
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,960
You can put in whatever meat you like.

66
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,000
It's just a common dish.

67
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,639
If you talk about authenticity,

68
00:03:20,759 --> 00:03:22,840
everyone can claim theirs
is the most authentic.

69
00:03:23,199 --> 00:03:24,080
In my opinion,

70
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,960
I'm just trying to imitate the taste
my father taught me.

71
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,960
You're right.
The taste of home is the most authentic.

72
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,240
But then,

73
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,759
your sign also says "Zhengzong."
*[Authentic]

74
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,719
Isn't that bragging too?

75
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:37,759
Yeah.

76
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,520
My father opened this shop.

77
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:40,919
My father's name is Wang Zhengzong.

78
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:47,120
Are you here just
because of those two characters?

79
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:48,639
Haha!

80
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:50,280
Drink up.

81
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:57,000
Gosh.

82
00:03:58,719 --> 00:03:59,960
What am I supposed to say about this?

83
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:08,220
(Jiang Yang)

84
00:04:08,879 --> 00:04:09,680
Hello.

85
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:10,800
(Ji Yu)

86
00:04:11,599 --> 00:04:13,599
Shi Guang is not beside you, right?

87
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,280
No, why?

88
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,920
I just heard

89
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,199
your dad got out of prison.

90
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:24,959
(Ji Yu)

91
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,519
Ji Yu?

92
00:04:31,079 --> 00:04:32,160
Are you still there?

93
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:33,879
(Are you okay?)

94
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,399
So soon?

95
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,480
I thought he'd be in there for life.

96
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:46,040
I'm afraid he'll come after you.

97
00:04:46,399 --> 00:04:47,759
Why don't you stay at my house?

98
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:49,040
(With me and Shi Guang here,)

99
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:50,160
(you'll be safer.)

100
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,759
We'll see.

101
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,680
He wouldn't dare
to do anything to me anyway.

102
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:56,560
Okay.

103
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:58,240
Then

104
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,560
be careful.

105
00:05:30,759 --> 00:05:31,399
Silly guy.

106
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,360
It's just a minor wound.

107
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,680
There's no need to bandage it.

108
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,199
I'm coming in.

109
00:06:03,839 --> 00:06:05,160
I thought you were afraid of the dark.

110
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,360
Why is it so dark in here?

111
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:18,040
Why did you remove the bandage?

112
00:06:18,199 --> 00:06:19,480
It'll get infected.

113
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,560
I won't die from that.

114
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,959
That won't do either.

115
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,879
It may leave a scar.

116
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:31,960
I got it as a kid after my dad beat me
when he was drunk.

117
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,360
I have one here too.

118
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,560
Every time he was drunk,

119
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:43,160
he would drag me out of bed and beat me.

120
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,639
I slept with the lights on

121
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,360
so I could keep an eye on him.

122
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,079
But it's okay.

123
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,360
People have

124
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,600
to adapt to their environment.

125
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,759
You're not obligated
to pay for other people's mistakes.

126
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:07,959
Ji Yu.

127
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,040
If a dish is bad,

128
00:07:11,199 --> 00:07:12,759
throw it in the trash.

129
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,199
There's no need
to force yourself to eat it.

130
00:07:24,199 --> 00:07:25,759
Tonight, sleep with the lights on.

131
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:27,000
How will you sleep

132
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:28,959
with the lights on?

133
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,160
I'll watch over you.

134
00:07:35,140 --> 00:07:37,620
♪I'm drenched under the heavy rain♪

135
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:39,980
♪But I remain silent♪

136
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:45,180
♪Who can tolerate
my eccentric personality?♪

137
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:45,800
Good night.

138
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:54,060
♪I care too much about right and wrong♪

139
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:58,060
♪Like complex polarized colours♪

140
00:07:58,060 --> 00:08:00,460
♪I can't sketch out
the original network♪

141
00:08:00,460 --> 00:08:04,430
♪Am I your first choice?♪

142
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,399
(Why are you looking for me?)

143
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:07,920
(Regarding Ji Yu's situation,)

144
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,920
(how much do you know?)

145
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:14,180
♪Let's give each other
our last blessing♪

146
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,759
(I feel a bit sorry for her.)

147
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:18,500
♪You've said countless times
that we're not right for each other♪

148
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,060
♪But I still struggle for an outcome♪

149
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:25,060
♪Is there medicine
that can heal my new wound?♪

150
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:27,519
(I want to understand her more.)

151
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:33,380
♪The deeper we immerse,
the lonelier we become♪

152
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:35,559
(I always thought)

153
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,720
(you were full of energy like the sun.)

154
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,559
(But I didn't expect)

155
00:08:39,559 --> 00:08:41,600
(underneath that optimistic appearance,)

156
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,919
(you carry so many painful memories.)

157
00:08:46,399 --> 00:08:48,840
(But from now on, as long as I'm here,)

158
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,679
(I won't let you get hurt.)

159
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,440
These useless program crew

160
00:08:56,879 --> 00:08:58,600
can't even handle a judge.

161
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,360
They didn't expect Mr. Wang
to intervene.

162
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,559
When they initially approached him,

163
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:04,320
Mr. Wang refused firmly.

164
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:06,960
Who knew Shi Guang
would stumble upon such luck

165
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:08,360
and benefit from it for free.

166
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,960
Lucky, huh?

167
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,600
Bring the program director to me.

168
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:15,159
I want to see how lucky he really is.

